cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DL, cs.LG, cs.SY. 

This paper discusses a research project focused on managing the complexity of interdependent software components, specifically Debian packages. The project involves the development of tools for distribution-wide quality assurance and dependency management. These topics are closely related to software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DL). The project also involves machine learning and data mining techniques (cs.LG) for analyzing package dependencies and predicting potential issues. Finally, the project aims to improve system reliability and stability (cs.SY) by addressing the upgrade problem.
